name: chicagotribune
text:
RT @John_Kass: How to drive politics out of your head before Christmas? Make my onion soup. It's all about the stock. My "What are you cooking for Christmas Dinner?"column @chicagotribune
https://t.co/NYe6J4IYjH

name: chicagotribune
text: The sandwich is made of two slices of Spam and Oreo cookies, topped with mayonnaise. https://t.co/cmNT0Sap7b

name: chicagotribune
text: “I ran the Chicago Marathon before, and this is like the marathon that never ends. Nurses are just running on fumes right now. I want to say that I’m numb. I don’t feel anything. I’m just going through the motions, just to get it done.” https://t.co/29CjFLqekl

name: chicagotribune
text: A week after the first shipment of Pfizer’s coronavirus vaccine arrived in Illinois, about 63,000 health care workers across the state have received their first of two doses of the immunization, Gov. J.B. Pritzker’s office said. https://t.co/BK19D2VmSi

name: chicagotribune
text: A federal advisory panel has voted to put people 75 and older and essential workers like firefighters, teachers and grocery store workers next in line for the COVID-19 vaccine. https://t.co/zIBsozOoCO

name: chicagotribune
text: The House easily passed a $900 billion COVID-19 relief package Monday night. A Senate vote is expected soon. https://t.co/0zm3zPg2m1

name: chicagotribune
text: Shoe retailers say they’re confident business will bounce back. But some think a shift to more casual looks, already underway before COVID-19, is here to stay. https://t.co/GWlX69cVsZ

name: chicagotribune
text: Fox News, Newsmax shoot down aired election claims after voting machine companies threaten legal action https://t.co/EDVQav9T17

name: chicagotribune
text: The arrival of the two-week winter break amid worrisome COVID-19 rates across the region is adding up to a holiday season fraught with anxiety and uncertainty about what school will look like when classes resume in January. https://t.co/SAC81c28Mp

name: chicagotribune
text: Bring on the December holidays ... during a pandemic. https://t.co/COwsB6HqS3
